commentTextItems.html: slower ball cut away and it finds a gap in between the field. Both batsmen punch the air in delight as they sprint through for the winning runs.

commentPostTextItems.html: What an amazing victory for West Indies. New Zealand always looked in control but Ramdin managed to steer the tourists home to victory. Credit to the grounds staff here at Christchurch who managed to get the ground playable this evening after some terrible weather earlier in the day.

After the first match was washed out, West Indies take a 1-0 lead in the series with the 3rd ODI scheduled for 2.00pm on the 7th January in Wellington. Do join us then but for now from Pat Culpan and Callum Stewart here at cricinfo it's good night.

commentTextItems.html: cut away to backward point and they scamper the single. Elliot throws at the stumps and just misses. They take one and the scores are level

commentPostTextItems.html: Everyone in now for New Zealand

commentTextItems.html: he tries to cut away the wide one and gets a bottom edge through to McCullum. He rolls the ball at the stumps and misses as Ramdin retreats back to his crease. He would have been out! No run
slower ball which is clubbed away but only to short midwicket. No run
short of a length and it gets pulled over midwicket and they take two. Picked up in the deep
cut away to gully and they take one to keep Ramdin on strike

commentPostTextItems.html: Southee is going to be handed the last over here. Only 4 runs needed for the tourists

headshotImage.longCaption: Jeetan Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: leans back and takes another swipe and he connects again! The ball sails high over extra cover and takes a couple of hops before jumping over the rope. Back to back boundaries and West Indies in the driving seat
another full toss from Patel and Ramdin connects pulling the ball through midwicket. Four runs
jabbed away to the covers and they scramble one
another ugly full toss from Patel about waist high. He goes for the pull shot which drops agonisingly short of Taylor at deep midwicket but he stops the boundary
full toss and he comes down the track to place the ball past cover and they manage to turn without slipping and pick up two runs
prodded away towards point and another one added to the total

commentPostTextItems.html: 18 runs needed from 12 balls. Still could go either way here. Surely not another tied match...

headshotImage.caption: Ramnaresh Sarwan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ramnaresh Sarwan player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: goes hard at the flashing cut and edges it over the infield and it races away to the boundary where Flynn makes a good diving stop but they pick up three
superb improvisation! Ramdin shuffles across his stumps and flicks the ball on the half volley past the fielder diving at short fine leg.
miss times the big shot which fall short of long-off and they pick up a single
chipped away to long-off
cut away through point and they turn quick for two
hit on the half-volley straight back over the bowlers head and there's enough on it to go all the way for six.

commentPostTextItems.html: The West Indies are still in this. 30 runs off 18 balls

commentTextItems.html: fuller ball dug out to short leg and they sprint through one
hit in the air past the diving Taylor at midwicket and picked up at long-on

stories.seoTitle: 'The wickets in hand paid off' - Sarwan
stories.summary: West Indies batsman Ramnaresh Sarwan has said he was confident of the team's chances in the second ODI against New Zealand in Christchurch, even after coming under severe pressure towards the end of the chase.
